article.headline: Cornell 34, Columbia 14
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Shane Kilcoyne returned the opening kickoff 94 yards for a touchdown, and Brian Walters ran back a punt 82 yards with 1:45 remaining in the first quarter to help Cornell beat Columbia 34-14 in Ivy League play Saturday. Cornell quarterback Stephen Liuzza was 17-of-26 for 163 yards with no interceptions, and he ran 85 yards and two touchdowns. Columbia wide receiver Austin Knowlin caught nine passes for 73 yards and scored both of the Lions' touchdowns. Cornell took a 21-0 lead in the first before Knowlin scored Columbia's first touchdown on a 3-yard pass from Craig Hormann at 11:46 in the second. Hormann was 16-of-34 for 134 yards with no interceptions. Peter Zell kicked a 28-yard field goal for the Big Red as time expired in the first half, giving Cornell a 24-7 lead. Cornell made it 34-7 in the third on a 14-yard run by Liuzza and a 31-yard field goal by Zell. The Lions completed the scoring in the fourth when they moved 87 yards in eight plays capped by Knowlin's second TD on an 8-yard pass from Shane Kelly. Kelly was 14-of-23 for 171 yard with no interceptions.
